title: Fleetwood Mac - King Biscuit Flower Hour, Passaic, NJ - 1975-05-
description:
Fleetwood Mac
1975-05-03
Capitol Theatre, Passaic, NJ


unofficial soundboard recording - excellent quality

WBCN-FM Broadcast King Biscuit Flower Hour

Lineage:

Master 'off air' FM Reel [Maxell LNE25-7 (Revox) 7 1/2ips 1/4 track] --> Tascam CD-RW2000 --> EAC --> CDWAV --> FLAC



Tracklist:

01 - Radio Broadcast Announcement
02 - Intro	
03 - Station Man
04 - Spare Me A Little
05 - Rhiannon
06 - Landslide
07 - I'm So Afraid
08 - World Turning
09 - Don't Let Me Down Again
10 - Hypnotized


Lineup:

Lindsey Buckingham - guitar, vocals
Mick Fleetwood - drums
Christine McVie - keyboards, vocals
John McVie - bass
Stevie Nicks - vocals, percussion


Notes:

Supposedly recorded at Capitol Theatre, Passaic, New Jersey, in May 1975. There are also rumours that it actually was recorded in 1976 at the New Haven Coliseum. This is similar to Don't You Let Me Down Again, New Jersey 1975, Albatross - But Not Around My Neck Please, King Buscuit Flower Hour, and Rockhoppers '76
